  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop your <strong>waxy potatoes</strong> in half, lengthways</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to a baking tray with your <strong>ground smoked paprika</strong>, a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for an initial 15 min or until starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681286205201-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681286205201-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681286205201-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681286205201-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1681286205201-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the potatoes are cooking, heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and cook for 2-3 min or until toasted and lightly golden</p><p>Once golden, transfer them to a plate and reserve the pan</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
